  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency WASH interventions to drought-affected population in Central South Somalia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of this $4m UNICEF project is to provide life-saving water and sanitation services to 180,000 drought-affected Somalis. The CERF funding will enable UNICEF to provide 7.5l of drinking water per person per day to 180,000 Somalis through water trucking for four to six weeks. In addition, UNICEF will drill five new boreholes and additionally repair 20 water sources. Twenty-five health facilities will also receive emergency water supply. UNICEF will construct or repair 400 latrines, giving 12,000 people access to safe and dignified toilets with functional handwashing facilities. UNICEF will also distribute water and sanitation kits, including water treatment supplies, serving 180,000 persons, and conduct hygiene promotion activities. Among the 180,000 persons targeted, UNICEF expects to reach 35,133 women and 52,322 girls.</narrative>
  </description>
